approve(address,uint256).details: Authorize a third party operator to manage one particular asset

balanceOf(address).details: Gets the balance of the specified address

params._owner: address to query the balance of

balanceOf(address).return: uint256 representing the amount owned by the passed address

erc721ByIndex(uint256).return: The ERC721 identifier for the `_index` of the NFT, (sort order not specified)

erc721OfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).details: Throws if `_index` >= `balanceOf(_owner)` or if `_owner` is the zero address, representing invalid NFTs.

params._owner: An address where we are interested in NFTs owned by them

erc721OfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).return: The ERC721 identifier for the `_index` of the NFT assigned to `_owner`,  (sort order not specified)

isApprovedForAll(address,address).details: Query whether an address has been authorized to move any assets on behalf of someone else

params._operator: the address that might be authorized
params._owner: the address that provided the authorization

isApprovedForAll(address,address).return: bool true if the operator has been authorized to move any assets

isAuthorized(address,uint256).details: Query if an operator can move an asset.

params._assetId: the asset that has been `approved` for transfer
params._operator: the address that might be authorized

isAuthorized(address,uint256).return: bool true if the asset has been approved by the owner

params._assetId: uint256 ID of the asset to be transferred
params._from: address that currently owns an asset
params._to: address to receive the ownership of the asset

safeTransferFrom(address,address,uint256.details: Securely transfers the ownership of a given asset from one address to another address, calling the method `onNFTReceived` on the target address if there's code associated with it

params._assetId: uint256 ID of the asset to be transferred
params._from: address that currently owns an asset
params._to: address to receive the ownership of the asset
params._userData: bytes arbitrary user information to attach to this transfer

setApprovalForAll(address,bool).details: Authorize a third party operator to manage (send) msg.sender's asset

params._authorized: bool set to true to authorize, false to withdraw authorization

supportsInterface(bytes4).details: implement supportsInterface(bytes4) using a lookup table

tokenURI(uint256).details: Throws if `_erc721Id` is not a valid NFT. URIs are defined in RFC 3986. The URI may point to a JSON file that conforms to the "ERC721 Metadata JSON Schema".

totalSupply().details: Gets the total amount of assets stored by the contract
totalSupply().return: uint256 representing the total amount of assets

transferFrom(address,address,uint256).details: Transfers the ownership of a given asset from one address to another address Warning! This function does not attempt to verify that the target address can send erc721Ids.

params._assetId: uint256 ID of the asset to be transferred
params._to: address to receive the ownership of the asset

erc721OfOwnerByIndex(address,uint256).notice: Enumerate NFTs assigned to an owner

tokenURI(uint256).notice: A distinct Uniform Resource Identifier (URI) for a given asset.
